configuration.note: All activation evaluations use Neuronpedia API. Activation threshold is dynamically calculated from top 10 high-activating API exemplars (average of max activations / 2). Generation Evaluation uses top 10 high-activating exemplars. Prediction Evaluation uses selected exemplars directly from API (excluding top 10), with activation values already available (no API calls needed for activations). model_name and sae_path are kept for record-keeping only and are not used for any calculations.

explanation.description: Feature 24497 (Layer 7) is a lexical detector for the whitespace-prefixed tokens ‘ tab’ and ‘ tabs’, with case/form sensitivity and subtoken behavior. Across 9 tests, standalone lower-case ‘ tab’ consistently shows the highest activation (~7.7–8.3), plural ‘ tabs’ is lower (~5.7–7.1), and ‘ tab’ as a subword prefix (e.g., in “tablix”, “tabular”) also activates (~6.2–7.1) while the suffix tokens remain ~0; capitalized/all-caps variants activate but are reduced (‘ Tab’=7.31, ‘ Tabs’=6.94, ‘ TAB’=4.72). Negative controls where no separate ‘ tab’ subtoken exists (e.g., “table”, “tablet”) yield ~0, indicating context-independent lexical triggering governed by tokenization.
explanation.evidence:
- Test 1: 'Click the tab to open new tabs in the tablix report.' → activation 8.3125 at ' tab' (supports H1; ‘ tabs’=7.1250; ‘ tab’ in ‘tablix’=7.1250; ‘lix’=0.0000)
- Test 2: 'Press the tab key to indent.' → activation 7.8125 at ' tab' (supports H2; neighbors near zero: ‘ key’=0.1572)
- Test 3: 'The table was converted into a tablix for the report.' → activation 6.1562 at ' tab' (supports H3; ‘ table’=0.0000; ‘lix’=0.0000)
- Test 4: 'Click the Tab, press TAB, then open the tab-bar and view the tabs.' → activation 8.1875 at ' tab' (supports H4; case ranking: ‘ Tab’=7.3125 > ‘ TAB’=4.7188 < ‘ tab’; ‘ tabs’=6.0938; ‘-bar’=0.0000)
- Test 5: 'Select the tab to view all tabs in the tabular report.' → activation 8.1250 at ' tab' (supports H1/H3; ‘ tabs’=7.0625; ‘ tab’ in ‘tabular’=6.1875; ‘ular’=0.0000)
- Test 6: 'Use a tab delimiter instead of tabs.' → activation 7.6562 at ' tab' (supports H2; ‘ tabs’=5.7188; ‘ delimiter’=0.1201)
- Test 7: 'Open a new tab.' → activation 8.3125 at ' tab' (supports H1)
- Test 8: 'The tablet crashed today.' → activation 0.0000 across tokens (supports H3; ‘ tablet’=0.0000)
- Test 9: 'Open the Tabs menu.' → activation 6.9375 at ' Tabs' (supports H4; capitalized plural activates but below lower-case ‘ tab’)

prediction_evaluation.note: Prediction Evaluation uses selected exemplars directly from API (excluding top 10 used for Generation Evaluation). Exemplars are categorized into high, medium, and low activation groups from remaining exemplars, and randomly selected from each group. Activation values are already available from exemplars, so no API calls are needed to get activations. This avoids bias from explanation text and ensures diverse activation levels in evaluation examples.
